aa(lp19
VBut what's floating there today are not just clouds of galaxies
p20
aVbut also clouds of plastic.
p21
aVThese are the footprints we're leaving on the planet.
p22
aVThey're signs of an era
p23
aVin which the behavior of some humans is making a global impact
p24
aVon our ecosystems.
p25
aVThis era is called the Anthropocene.
p26
aVThere's also another type of toxic clouds that float in the air,
p27
aVlike the ones that form from carbon dioxide emissions
p28
aVand from the burning of fossil fuels \u2014 oil, carbon, gas \u2014
p29
aVclouds that, when we see them,
p30
aVpollute our dreams.
p31
aVI don't know about all of you,
p32
aVbut I've always dreamed of floating among the clouds.
p33
aVMaybe today we can imagine together other types of clouds,
p34
aVclouds we can live with.
