aVBut how can we learn to float among the clouds?
p48
aVAs an artist, I thought we could start building a flying museum.
p49
aVYou're probably wondering: With plastic bags?
p50
aa(lp51
VIn 2007, with a community of people all over the world,
p52
aVwe began to collect used plastic bags \u2014
p53
aVnot new ones.
p54
aVAnd we washed them,
p55
aVwe cut them up,
p56
aVwe glued them together,
p57
aVand we began to draw on them,
p58
aVcreating a huge canvas.
p59
aVWe made a collection of drawings,
p60
aVof personal stories
p61
aVand of friendships.
p62
aVAnd when you join them,
p63
aVbend them and fold them,
p64
aVit creates a space full of air.
p65
aVWhen the sun comes up from the horizon,
p66
aVthe museum rises up to the sky.
p67
aVThat's why we call it, "The Aero-Solar Museum."
p68
aVAnd from this simple idea,
p69
aVwe learned how to float in the air in a radically new way,
p70
aVwithout using any type of fuel.
p71
aVThe difference in temperature between the interior and the exterior
p72
aVis what makes us rise up.
p73
aVThat way,
p74
aVwe don't use fossil fuels or helium or hydrogen;
p75
aVwe don't use solar panels
p76
aVor batteries or motors.
p77
aVWe discovered a way that's simple, clean and accessible to the whole world
p78
aVto lift ourselves up.
